{
  "stem": "22869.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It meant-- it meant really a lot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It like become a-- a-- like a new hope.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There is somebody I can speak to who is your flesh and blood.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It gave me a little faith, awakening in myself, even if it was very temporary, that maybe there was a chance that someday maybe we will see freedom.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was just a glimpse of such a thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it awakened in me something that I was missing for the last seven weeks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because nobody really close to me from home was around me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So finding them and seeing the fact that they're alive gave me like a little boost.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By that time, we were so dehumanized.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tried to explain this many times to people that have no concept really what Birkenau or Auschwitz or a concentration camp as such was.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You cannot under circumstances that are beyond description of suffering-- you cannot be day and night hungry and thirsty and be sick, first of all, even maintain your normal way of thinking.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You lose-- your-- your brain like, slows down, or you become detached from the eye.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There is no such thing anymore that today, an intelligent person starts thinking in the realm of who am I?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What am I?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You lost your complete contact that there is such a thing as you, and God, and belief, and faith, because you are at the point that you see this is-- this is your end.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, you uttered the word 'oh God, help me.' As they say, there is no atheist in a foxhole.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was no such a thing as a person not being religious in a manner of thinking, oh God, help me.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
